[1] China, Xinjiang
Date: Thu, 8 Jun 2006
From: Mary Marshall <tropical.forestry@btinternet.com>
Source: Xinhuanet, 7 Jun 2006 [edited]
<http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2006-06/08/content_4660598.htm>

China has discovered a new H5N1 bird flu case in poultry in the
western Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, the Ministry of Agriculture
(MOA) said on Wednesday [7 Jun 2006].
The case was identified after domestic poultry at a farm in
Xinjiang's Hetian County died of an unclear illness. [see map of
Hetian/Hotan at
<http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2003-04/03/content_815413.htm>].
The dead poultry were confirmed to have been infected with the bird
flu virus on Wednesday after testing at the national bird flu laboratory.
The MOA has sent expert teams to Hetian to control any possible outbreak.
An emergency mechanism has been launched and the local veterinary
departments have set up examination stations to disinfect people and
vehicles into and out of the affected area.
