[3] Romania, suspected
Date: Thu, 8 Jun 2006
From: Mary Marshall <tropical.forestry@btinternet.com>
Source: Sofia News Agency, 7 Jun 2006 [edited]
<http://www.novinite.com/view_news.php?id=64651>

The latest site with the lethal H5N1 bird flu in Romania was
confirmed to be just 40 km away from the northern Bulgarian border,
in Gurgevo province.[Probably Bulgarian for the Romanian province
Giurgiu; see map at
<http://www.aboutromania.com/maps3.html> - Mod.AS]
A statement posted on a municipal website denounces earlier refusals
on the availability of the lethal virus in the area.
The site with detected infection is near the village of Balbukata,
and Romanian authorities are affirming it has been disinfected. The
settlement is under quarantine and some 800 birds were culled,
Bulgarian National Radio (BNR) informed.
